- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for NLP tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques for training the NLP models. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of NLP for text analysis and information extraction. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper mentions the use of neural networks for some of the NLP tasks.
